data.text: Olivia d’Abo was destined to be a free spirit! Sired by ’60s model Maggie London and Mike d’Abo, lead vocalist of the cosmic rockers Manfred Mann’s Earth Band, the gorgeous girl grew up in a groovy environment. Her real-life training in psychedelia made her all the more adorable as the hippie-chick hottie on the super ’70s flashback series The Wonder Years (1988-1993). Like every flower child worth her weight in wheat germ, Olivia embraces the concept of letting it all hang out! Perhaps that’s why she showed off her pokies and butt cheeks via soaking wet skivvies in the drama Bullies (1986). After flashing her cans in the thriller Into the Fire (1988), the crime saga Bank Robber (1993) and the drama The Last Good Time (1994), the arousing actress bumped bare breasts with Lora Zane during a dyke-namic fantasy scene in the comedy Live Nude Girls (1995). We had both a Good Time and saw Live Nude Girls! In addition to donning alluring attire in Conan the Destroyer (1984) and slinky bikinis in Greedy (1994) and The Triangle (2001), d’Abo looked d’Lightful in the movies Clean Slate (1994) and Dad’s Week Off (1997) as well as on the NBC sitcom The Single Guy (1995-1997). Speaking of the boob-tube, sapphic sophisticates will recall Olivia as Neve Campbell’s foxy female love interest on Party of Five (1999). Now, that’s a party of two everyone can enjoy! Since then, the blonde babe displayed her bra-clad cleavage in The Enemy (2001)—which seems pretty friendly to us!
